The paper discusses the use of vehicular networks for collaborative content distribution, which involves communication protocols and network infrastructure, making it likely to fall under the Network and Information Security (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the need for security certificates, which further supports this sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential cost reduction of cellular-based communication, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of V2V communication, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the simulation study, which could fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
